column5: This is what's left of my Walleye after a Trophy Muskie tried to eat it, after 15 minuted of battlin'..I was hoping to get them both in the net but at the last minute the Muskie jumped and threw the Walleye, I left the Walleye in the water for a while but the Muskie did'nt come back.

Yes dont you hate it when that happens !!!!!! that sucks cause your walleye,is now all mangled up  ,and dam !! you lost that big muskie....   oh well it could have been worse,you might have not caught anything,at lesat you fought that big boy for 15mins and gave you a good work out.  ..cheers
sad looking walleye.Too bad the muskie would not cooperate
Sad for sure , he was part of my limit of four
Ahhhhhh, very nice!  Too bad about the 'ski.
May not be much of a dinner 'eye but a hell of a story.  I'd say that's a fair trade.
Looks like it tried to fillet it for you! Be happy!
I hope it happens again in the coming weeks,  but I want to win th battle next time..!!
very exciting when something like that happens (unless of course you needed that fish to survive...then it sucks)
Sounds like heart pounding action! I've been waiting for something like that to happen!! It has happened with pike but never with Musky!
Same here it's happened with pike before but never ..until yesterday  happen with a Muskie..  ZZZZZZZING!
